import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.scatter(series_data['X'], series_data['Y'], label=series)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    means = data.groupby('Series').mean()
    stds = data.groupby('Series').std()
    
    ind = np.arange(len(means))
    width = 0.35
    
    plt.bar(ind - width/2, means['X'], width, label='Mean X', yerr=stds['X'])
    plt.bar(ind + width/2, means['Y'], width, label='Mean Y', yerr=stds['Y'])
    
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.xticks(ind, means.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    series_list = data['Series'].unique()
    for series in series_list:
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.hist(series_data['X'], alpha=0.5, label=f'X {series}')
        plt.hist(series_data['Y'], alpha=0.5, label=f'Y {series}')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of X and Y for each series?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.plot(series_data['X'], series_data['Y'], label=series)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('X')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    series_list = data['Series'].unique()
    x_data = [data[data['Series'] == s]['X'] for s in series_list]
    y_data = [data[data['Series'] == s]['Y'] for s in series_list]

    plt.boxplot(x_data, positions=[i*2 for i in range(len(series_list))], widths=0.6, labels=series_list)
    plt.boxplot(y_data, positions=[i*2+1 for i in range(len(series_list))], widths=0.6)

    plt.xticks(rotation=45 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    plt.title("What is the difference between the four series?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
